Eskom to Boost Purchases From Independent Power Producers to 400 Megawatts

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-02-15T07:25:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/eskom-to-boost-purchases-from-independent-power-producers-to-400-megawatts.html
Eskom Holdings Ltd., the state-owned
South African electricity utility, plans to increase purchases
from independent power producers to 400 megawatts by the end of
the year, Transport Minister Sibusiso Ndebele said.  Eskom has so far signed agreements to buy 277 megawatts
from independent producers, he said in a speech distributed to
reporters in  Cape Town  today. The state-owned utility will spend
549 billion rand on new infrastructure by 2017, Ndebele said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  